    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>286 Nth 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Sunday</date> morning</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>February 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1856</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Robert Lyon Esqre</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would have readily complied with<lb/> your request, of which I was
                    <sic>apprized</sic> yesterday afternoon,<lb/> if the Managers of the Foster-home
                had not <sic>preceeded</sic><lb/> your intention, by resolving that the proceedings
                of their<lb/> first anniversary, should be published, in the Occident,<lb/> at their
                expense. I have already transmitted to<lb/> their Secretary, the copy of my address,
                and I consider<lb/> to have thereby lost any right to its disposal.</p>
            <p>You will, undoubtedly approve of my conduct, and rest<lb/> assured that had it been
                otherwise, it would have afforded<lb/> me pleasure to have read my remarks in your
                valuable<lb/> Periodical.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">S. Morais</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>R. Lyon Esqre.</addressee>
            </p>
